\begin_layout Standard
BigBlind is here a global variable, that gets initialized immediatelly,
 when the DLL gets loaded.
 But the function gws uses a callback-pointer, that gets initialized later
 with one of the first messages from OpenHoldem to the DLL.
 So you dereference an undefined pointer and get a memory-access-error.
\end_layout

